WEBVTT

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:03.350
Good morning, family. How are y'all

00:00:03.360 --> 00:00:05.349
doing today? I'm here again with

00:00:05.359 --> 00:00:06.550
my wife, Diana.

00:00:06.960 --> 00:00:08.790
We're excited to be here as we have

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:10.549
some things on our heart. The Lord told

00:00:10.559 --> 00:00:12.150
me, 'Brandon, I want you to

00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:14.950
talk to my people again about the

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:17.910
refiner's fire, where they

00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:20.630
are, and how to

00:00:20.640 --> 00:00:23.830
get to the next level.'Many people think praying and reading the Bible gets them to the next level,

00:00:23.840 --> 00:00:26.790
but

00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:29.269
those

00:00:29.279 --> 00:00:31.269
are

00:00:31.279 --> 00:00:34.790
the fundamentals. We use

00:00:34.800 --> 00:00:37.110
the fundamentals

00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:39.030
day-to-day.

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:41.910
A professional athlete

00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:45.110
does the fundamentals

00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:47.670
that make him a champion in

00:00:47.670 --> 00:00:47.680
a

00:00:47.680 --> 00:00:50.310
major game like the World

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:53.029
Series; without

00:00:53.029 --> 00:00:53.039
them,

00:00:53.039 --> 00:00:55.029
they'll never become a champion in the

00:00:55.029 --> 00:00:55.039
end game.

00:00:55.039 --> 00:00:58.389
It's the day-to-day fundamentals

00:00:58.389 --> 00:00:58.399
that

00:00:58.399 --> 00:01:00.709
make

00:01:00.709 --> 00:01:00.719
you

00:01:00.719 --> 00:01:03.750
a champion.

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:06.630
The major test in

00:01:06.640 --> 00:01:09.830
life is the refiner's fire that

00:01:09.830 --> 00:01:09.840
takes

00:01:09.840 --> 00:01:12.710
us from

00:01:12.720 --> 00:01:15.670
glory to glory. If

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:19.350
you don't do the ABCs and

00:01:19.350 --> 00:01:19.360
1-2-3s,

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:22.550
you'll never pass the test.

00:01:22.550 --> 00:01:22.560
I

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:24.469
once

00:01:24.469 --> 00:01:24.479
went

00:01:24.479 --> 00:01:25.749
through a really hard

00:01:25.759 --> 00:01:29.830
time and thought, 'Where is the

00:01:29.830 --> 00:01:29.840
Lord?'I

00:01:29.840 --> 00:01:32.469
felt like everything was

00:01:32.479 --> 00:01:35.350
stripped away while going through a

00:01:35.350 --> 00:01:35.360
dark

00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:38.950
valley. I cried

00:01:38.960 --> 00:01:42.630
myself to sleep many nights, not

00:01:42.640 --> 00:01:45.270
knowing I was being tested. It

00:01:45.280 --> 00:01:47.590
was the refining fire. He is the

00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:51.590
potter, and we are the clay. We have

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:54.310
this treasure in earthen vessels so that

00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:56.069
the excellency of the power will be

00:01:56.079 --> 00:01:58.149
known of Him and not of us.

00:01:58.159 --> 00:02:01.190
You need to understand it's

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:03.429
Him in us.

00:02:03.439 --> 00:02:06.550
I'm just a person like you, but

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:09.190
He will use you in the Kingdom if you

00:02:09.200 --> 00:02:11.029
yield to Him. You have to

00:02:11.039 --> 00:02:13.990
be a vessel that's been tried. You will

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.990
not walk in the greater glory and

00:02:17.280 --> 00:02:18.949
manifestations without being on the

00:02:18.959 --> 00:02:23.110
potter's wheel. It's like when

00:02:23.110 --> 00:02:23.120
Lynne

00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:25.350
Hammond had a visitation. She

00:02:25.350 --> 00:02:25.360
spoke

00:02:25.360 --> 00:02:27.830
about

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:30.630
a manifestation of Jesus where He gave her

00:02:30.640 --> 00:02:35.030
a song: 'Make me better, make me pure,

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:38.550
by the fire that does refine. Where the

00:02:38.560 --> 00:02:40.949
breath of God is sweeter, there His

00:02:40.959 --> 00:02:44.070
brightest glory shines. Lift me high up

00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:46.390
to the mountain into fellowship with

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:48.710
Thee, and in that light I'll see the

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:51.190
fountain of the blood which cleanseth

00:02:51.200 --> 00:02:51.750
me.'I

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:52.949
love that song;

00:02:52.959 --> 00:02:55.110
it came

00:02:55.110 --> 00:02:55.120
directly

00:02:55.120 --> 00:02:57.830
from Jesus, singing to her

00:02:57.830 --> 00:02:57.840
while

00:02:57.840 --> 00:03:00.150
she was going through a refining fire. These

00:03:00.150 --> 00:03:00.160
are

00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:02.229
the

00:03:02.239 --> 00:03:04.869
fundamentals of life.

00:03:04.879 --> 00:03:06.550
The Lord showed me

00:03:06.560 --> 00:03:08.550
people are often tested every 20

00:03:08.560 --> 00:03:10.869
years. He showed me keys, dividing life into quarters. It was

00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:15.670
a

00:03:17.440 --> 00:03:21.190
beautiful revelation about how He tests us as we go

00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:24.229
from glory to glory.

00:03:26.879 --> 00:03:30.869
We are growing

00:03:30.879 --> 00:03:33.110
every single day. When we

00:03:33.110 --> 00:03:33.120
reach

00:03:33.120 --> 00:03:35.350
those major tests, we often don't even realize

00:03:35.350 --> 00:03:35.360
it.

00:03:35.360 --> 00:03:36.710
He told me,

00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:38.789
'I test you all the

00:03:38.789 --> 00:03:38.799
time.'That

00:03:38.799 --> 00:03:41.190
shapes

00:03:41.190 --> 00:03:41.200
our

00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:43.509
character on the potter's wheel,

00:03:43.519 --> 00:03:46.149
molding

00:03:46.159 --> 00:03:49.910
us

00:03:49.920 --> 00:03:52.229
and putting us through the fire.

00:03:52.239 --> 00:03:55.110
It's like refining gold

00:03:55.110 --> 00:03:55.120
and

00:03:55.120 --> 00:03:58.070
pulling out all the impurities.

00:03:58.080 --> 00:04:01.429
The more you work it,

00:04:01.439 --> 00:04:03.110
the purer the

00:04:03.120 --> 00:04:06.550
gold gets. As

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:08.869
vessels on the potter's wheel,

00:04:08.879 --> 00:04:12.229
God is making us into

00:04:12.239 --> 00:04:15.910
beautiful pieces of art for Him.

00:04:15.920 --> 00:04:18.150
The more we realize

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:21.270
it's about Him working in us, the

00:04:21.280 --> 00:04:23.670
more He can trust

00:04:23.670 --> 00:04:23.680
us.

00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:26.950
He is

00:04:26.960 --> 00:04:31.430
everything; I am a vessel

00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:33.670
chosen by God. We have this treasure in

00:04:33.670 --> 00:04:33.680
earthen

00:04:33.680 --> 00:04:35.670
vessels so that the excellency of

00:04:35.680 --> 00:04:37.749
the power will be known of Him and not

00:04:37.759 --> 00:04:39.189
of us. Amen.

00:04:39.199 --> 00:04:41.670
When we realize that, God

00:04:41.670 --> 00:04:41.680
will

00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:44.870
use and mold

00:04:44.870 --> 00:04:44.880
you

00:04:44.880 --> 00:04:46.629
further

00:04:46.629 --> 00:04:46.639
into

00:04:46.639 --> 00:04:48.950
that greater outpouring.

00:04:48.950 --> 00:04:48.960
I

00:04:48.960 --> 00:04:51.749
asked

00:04:51.759 --> 00:04:53.189
Him

00:04:53.199 --> 00:04:56.390
how we get

00:04:56.400 --> 00:04:59.189
to the greater manifestations

00:04:59.199 --> 00:05:02.550
of

00:05:02.560 --> 00:05:04.629
healings and demonstrations, and He

00:05:04.639 --> 00:05:06.550
said, 'Brandon, it's going to come

00:05:06.560 --> 00:05:08.390
through the fundamentals

00:05:08.390 --> 00:05:08.400
and

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:10.310
walking in love. You've got

00:05:10.320 --> 00:05:12.230
to master the foundation of love

00:05:12.240 --> 00:05:13.749
better.'The

00:05:13.759 --> 00:05:15.909
comment section is often a test for me

00:05:15.909 --> 00:05:15.919
when

00:05:15.919 --> 00:05:17.830
dealing with

00:05:17.840 --> 00:05:19.670
people. My son and wife tell me what's

00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:22.550
being said, and

00:05:22.560 --> 00:05:24.070
we're all growing

00:05:24.080 --> 00:05:26.870
together. This has been

00:05:26.870 --> 00:05:26.880
a

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:29.670
major change for us,

00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:31.909
like taking down

00:05:31.919 --> 00:05:35.350
all the false accounts claiming

00:05:35.350 --> 00:05:35.360
to be

00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:38.070
me, calling themselves 'Prophetic

00:05:38.070 --> 00:05:38.080
Biggs'and

00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:39.909
all these things. I don't call myself

00:05:39.919 --> 00:05:41.590
a prophet; I'm a watchman. I

00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:44.070
pray and tell you what

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:46.230
I hear and see.

00:05:47.600 --> 00:05:48.870
I just want to tell you what the

00:05:48.880 --> 00:05:50.790
Lord said: come on YouTube and tell

00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:50.800
everyone

00:05:50.800 --> 00:05:54.230
He's coming.

00:05:54.240 --> 00:05:56.870
I don't need a title; I

00:05:56.870 --> 00:05:56.880
just

00:05:56.880 --> 00:05:58.950
need you

00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:01.110
to hear that what I'm

00:06:01.120 --> 00:06:02.870
doing is telling you what He's told me

00:06:02.880 --> 00:06:04.309
to tell you. Whether you receive

00:06:04.309 --> 00:06:04.319
it

00:06:04.319 --> 00:06:06.790
is

00:06:06.790 --> 00:06:06.800
up

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:08.950
to

00:06:08.950 --> 00:06:08.960
you.

00:06:08.960 --> 00:06:10.950
Dealing with people

00:06:10.950 --> 00:06:10.960
these

00:06:10.960 --> 00:06:13.350
last few days has been a test. Diana spent

00:06:13.360 --> 00:06:15.990
24 hours

00:06:15.990 --> 00:06:16.000
straight

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:18.629
taking those accounts

00:06:18.639 --> 00:06:21.510
down because they were using

00:06:21.510 --> 00:06:21.520
the

00:06:21.520 --> 00:06:24.070
platform the Lord gave me

00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:28.070
to solicit

00:06:28.070 --> 00:06:28.080
money

00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:28.710
for

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:30.950
fake orphanages.

00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:37.350
They were asking for

00:06:37.360 --> 00:06:39.909
crypto,

00:06:39.919 --> 00:06:41.670
pretending

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:50.870
to be

00:06:50.870 --> 00:06:50.880
me

00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:53.670
and messaging people

00:06:53.680 --> 00:06:56.629
on WhatsApp.

00:06:56.639 --> 00:07:01.189
It was awful, and I'm really tired today.

00:07:01.840 --> 00:07:03.510
It was rough

00:07:03.520 --> 00:07:05.270
seeing that. Some accounts had tens of thousands of subscribers and millions of views. Hopefully, some people

00:07:13.749 --> 00:07:13.759
were

00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:22.629
reached, but they're using it

00:07:22.629 --> 00:07:22.639
to take

00:07:22.639 --> 00:07:24.629
money from people. It's

00:07:24.639 --> 00:07:27.110
very personal to me

00:07:27.120 --> 00:07:28.150
because we have a child with special

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:31.110
needs. To use children with

00:07:31.120 --> 00:07:33.909
special needs to solicit

00:07:33.919 --> 00:07:35.909
money is wrong. I'll

00:07:35.919 --> 00:07:38.790
never ask anyone for a dime. The

00:07:38.800 --> 00:07:40.309
Lord said, 'Freely you've been given,

00:07:40.319 --> 00:07:42.469
freely you give

00:07:42.469 --> 00:07:42.479
out.'He

00:07:42.479 --> 00:07:43.909
said if I feed His people,

00:07:43.919 --> 00:07:46.790
they will take care of me.

00:07:46.790 --> 00:07:46.800
I should

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:50.550
never ask for anything,

00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:53.189
just give. I've done

00:07:53.189 --> 00:07:53.199
my

00:07:53.199 --> 00:07:55.990
best

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:58.869
to warn you about

00:07:58.879 --> 00:08:01.189
the coming storms. A great

00:08:01.199 --> 00:08:03.350
shaking

00:08:03.350 --> 00:08:03.360
and

00:08:03.360 --> 00:08:07.270
food shortages are coming; these

00:08:07.270 --> 00:08:07.280
are

00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:09.670
birthing pains.

00:08:12.240 --> 00:08:15.589
Yesterday, I

00:08:15.589 --> 00:08:15.599
was

00:08:15.599 --> 00:08:18.710
praying over American Airlines

00:08:18.710 --> 00:08:18.720
and

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:21.110
United Airlines. I

00:08:21.120 --> 00:08:23.670
saw

00:08:23.680 --> 00:08:26.790
major planes in

00:08:26.800 --> 00:08:28.710
the sky and

00:08:28.710 --> 00:08:28.720
felt

00:08:29.990 --> 00:08:30.000
I

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:32.230
should

00:08:32.240 --> 00:08:33.909
pray over the airlines. I don't

00:08:33.919 --> 00:08:35.589
know why or if

00:08:35.589 --> 00:08:35.599
it's terrorist-related,

00:08:35.599 --> 00:08:37.670
but He said

00:08:37.670 --> 00:08:37.680
to

00:08:37.680 --> 00:08:39.670
pray. I get

00:08:39.670 --> 00:08:39.680
these

00:08:39.680 --> 00:08:40.949
pieces—warnings

00:08:40.959 --> 00:08:42.310
about power outages and

00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:45.990
food shortages.

00:08:49.839 --> 00:08:51.990
You could succumb to fear tactics,

00:08:51.990 --> 00:08:52.000
but

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:53.430
we

00:08:53.430 --> 00:08:53.440
must

00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:56.150
stay

00:08:56.150 --> 00:08:56.160
focused.

00:08:56.160 --> 00:08:57.990
They go in there

00:08:58.000 --> 00:08:59.430
and say, 'Hey, are you going to make a

00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:01.829
viral video? Talk about fear.'Boy, they

00:09:01.839 --> 00:09:03.590
sure like it. I mean, we laugh

00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:04.949
about it—my son does—because it's like,

00:09:04.959 --> 00:09:06.550
why don't you all want to hear about

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:07.910
the glory more than you want to

00:09:07.920 --> 00:09:09.670
hear about fear? You have to shake

00:09:09.680 --> 00:09:12.070
that all off. God is a good God,

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:13.350
a faithful God, and an

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:17.190
anointed God. He wants us to

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:19.190
live exceedingly abundantly above all

00:09:19.200 --> 00:09:20.870
that we'd ask or think. But I'm trying

00:09:20.880 --> 00:09:22.470
to tell you all, it's time to walk in

00:09:22.480 --> 00:09:24.550
victory about some things. It's time to

00:09:24.560 --> 00:09:25.910
lay hands on the sick and see

00:09:25.910 --> 00:09:25.920
them

00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:28.630
recover, for us to be the light and the

00:09:28.640 --> 00:09:31.430
salt, and stop walking in

00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:33.030
fear. We don't need to be walking in

00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:35.110
fear. I tell you these things not to

00:09:35.120 --> 00:09:37.670
walk in fear, but as a call to prayer to

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:39.990
say, 'Hey, listen, this is

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:42.070
sounding the alarm. Sound the alarm!

00:09:42.080 --> 00:09:43.509
Look at all these things that are coming.'But

00:09:43.509 --> 00:09:43.519
it seems

00:09:43.519 --> 00:09:46.070
people are

00:09:46.080 --> 00:09:47.509
more into that than they are when you tell

00:09:47.509 --> 00:09:47.519
them,

00:09:47.519 --> 00:09:49.030
'Hey, there's a glory

00:09:49.030 --> 00:09:49.040
coming.'In

00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:51.269
prayer at church tonight, we

00:09:51.279 --> 00:09:53.269
were hearing about Brother Hagin during

00:09:53.279 --> 00:09:56.310
the 1920s and some of the

00:09:56.320 --> 00:09:58.550
greats that I believe

00:09:58.560 --> 00:10:00.389
changed my life just by hearing some of

00:10:00.399 --> 00:10:02.550
the stories of what they did. Pastor

00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:05.350
Chip was talking about how they

00:10:05.360 --> 00:10:08.870
would pray by just giving God praise

00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:10.870
during the Great

00:10:10.880 --> 00:10:13.509
Depression.

00:10:13.519 --> 00:10:14.949
It's not the Great Tribulation yet,

00:10:14.959 --> 00:10:17.990
folks; during the

00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:20.550
Great Depression,

00:10:20.560 --> 00:10:22.389
they would

00:10:22.399 --> 00:10:25.350
pray and they never went without food.

00:10:25.360 --> 00:10:27.990
They never went without food one time

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:30.069
because they learned how to

00:10:30.079 --> 00:10:33.269
cultivate praise in their household.

00:10:33.279 --> 00:10:36.710
When praises go up, blessings come down.

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:39.670
So I want to teach you all

00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:42.470
that you've got to get into an atmosphere

00:10:42.480 --> 00:10:44.949
of thanksgiving and praise, being

00:10:44.959 --> 00:10:47.430
thankful for what the Lord has already

00:10:47.440 --> 00:10:50.150
provided in your life. You may not feel

00:10:50.160 --> 00:10:52.630
like He's done anything in your life;

00:10:52.640 --> 00:10:53.990
you may look and go, 'Well, look at

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:55.910
me and I don't have nothing. I'm poor as

00:10:55.920 --> 00:10:58.310
Job's turkey.'But you can be thankful

00:10:58.320 --> 00:11:00.949
for something. You start with that one

00:11:00.959 --> 00:11:04.389
thing and you

00:11:04.399 --> 00:11:07.190
be thankful all day long. 'God, I'm able

00:11:07.200 --> 00:11:09.509
to breathe. I took

00:11:09.519 --> 00:11:11.910
a breath today. My

00:11:11.910 --> 00:11:11.920
eyes—and

00:11:11.920 --> 00:11:14.389
you may be

00:11:14.389 --> 00:11:14.399
paralyzed—my

00:11:14.399 --> 00:11:17.190
eyes are moving. I can move my

00:11:17.190 --> 00:11:17.200
eyes.'You

00:11:17.200 --> 00:11:18.630
may not be able to move anything else,

00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:21.910
but you can move your eyes. Be thankful

00:11:21.920 --> 00:11:24.550
for any little thing, and I'm

00:11:24.560 --> 00:11:26.710
telling you, that's the key to the

00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:29.030
open door for the greater blessings.

00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:32.230
Being thankful. I'm talking to myself.

00:11:32.240 --> 00:11:33.829
There's so much that I feel the Lord has

00:11:33.839 --> 00:11:35.509
done for us in the last two or three

00:11:35.519 --> 00:11:37.670
months, and yet I take time

00:11:37.670 --> 00:11:37.680
to

00:11:37.680 --> 00:11:39.030
complain about certain things. The

00:11:39.040 --> 00:11:41.430
Lord said, 'Brandon, can't

00:11:41.440 --> 00:11:43.430
you be grateful about one

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:43.440
thing?'And

00:11:43.440 --> 00:11:46.150
He'll correct me. 'Oh

00:11:46.160 --> 00:11:49.110
Lord, I'm sorry. Forgive me. You've

00:11:49.120 --> 00:11:51.350
given so much to me. I have food in my

00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:53.590
belly. I have a roof over my head.

00:11:53.600 --> 00:11:56.069
My bills are

00:11:56.069 --> 00:11:56.079
paid.'You

00:11:56.079 --> 00:11:58.470
can give God praise for

00:11:58.480 --> 00:12:00.069
something,

00:12:00.079 --> 00:12:03.350
and when you do, blessings flow. The

00:12:03.360 --> 00:12:05.269
more you praise Him, the more blessings

00:12:05.279 --> 00:12:06.629
will flow. And I'm telling you, whenever

00:12:06.639 --> 00:12:10.069
I heard Pastor Chip talk about the Great

00:12:10.079 --> 00:12:12.310
Depression and he was saying that

00:12:12.320 --> 00:12:14.150
Brother Hagin and them never went

00:12:14.160 --> 00:12:17.110
without food because they always praised

00:12:17.120 --> 00:12:19.030
him for the little things. And for what

00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:21.590
I've seen coming—you think

00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:23.430
the Great Depression was bad in those

00:12:23.430 --> 00:12:23.440
storybooks—for

00:12:23.440 --> 00:12:24.949
what I have seen

00:12:24.959 --> 00:12:26.949
coming, folks, this is going to make the

00:12:26.959 --> 00:12:28.790
Great Depression look like a walk in the

00:12:28.800 --> 00:12:31.350
park because this generation doesn't

00:12:31.360 --> 00:12:33.350
understand how to even grow things in a

00:12:33.360 --> 00:12:36.150
garden. They don't know how to do

00:12:36.160 --> 00:12:37.590
most things. They're so used to

00:12:37.600 --> 00:12:39.430
going through McDonald's and getting

00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:41.190
their little Happy Meal or

00:12:41.200 --> 00:12:43.829
whatever. This is a different generation

00:12:43.839 --> 00:12:46.389
than it was 100 years ago.

00:12:46.399 --> 00:12:47.829
So, that's what I'm talking about.

00:12:47.839 --> 00:12:50.470
You've got to learn now

00:12:50.480 --> 00:12:53.110
how to live by faith so

00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:55.110
that you're able to operate when things

00:12:55.120 --> 00:12:57.110
get rough. You can't wait until things

00:12:57.120 --> 00:12:59.509
get rough

00:12:59.519 --> 00:13:01.670
and then start doing things

00:13:01.680 --> 00:13:03.190
and say, 'Well, we're going to start

00:13:03.200 --> 00:13:05.350
practicing it now.'Practice His

00:13:05.360 --> 00:13:07.269
presence today.

00:13:07.279 --> 00:13:10.150
Practice Him today. And so,

00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:11.269
tell them about that time

00:13:11.279 --> 00:13:12.949
whenever you had groceries

00:13:12.959 --> 00:13:14.550
show up as a little girl.

00:13:14.560 --> 00:13:18.710
Yeah. As a child, we grew up

00:13:18.720 --> 00:13:21.110
really poor. We lived in a

00:13:21.120 --> 00:13:23.750
car for a while. My parents didn't

00:13:23.760 --> 00:13:26.310
take help from the

00:13:26.320 --> 00:13:29.590
government or anything, so we lived

00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.590
in a car for a while. We ate ketchup

00:13:31.600 --> 00:13:34.069
packets for food—those free

00:13:34.079 --> 00:13:35.590
ketchup packets that you get out of

00:13:35.600 --> 00:13:38.150
McDonald's. We ate those. We lived

00:13:38.160 --> 00:13:39.829
in the car.

00:13:39.839 --> 00:13:40.870
For how long, though?

00:13:40.880 --> 00:13:43.269
Oh, for probably at least a

00:13:43.279 --> 00:13:43.750
year.

00:13:43.760 --> 00:13:46.310
Yeah, I remember I was really

00:13:46.320 --> 00:13:48.150
little, probably like four or

00:13:48.160 --> 00:13:48.870
five,

00:13:48.880 --> 00:13:51.670
maybe even younger. Homeless. Yeah.

00:13:51.680 --> 00:13:55.670
And I remember one time we were in

00:13:55.680 --> 00:13:57.670
the car, me and my older sister. We were

00:13:57.680 --> 00:13:59.430
sitting in the car and it was a hot

00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:03.750
summer day, and we were so hot. And

00:14:03.760 --> 00:14:05.829
we saw this soda machine in front of us.

00:14:07.279 --> 00:14:09.829
I

00:14:09.839 --> 00:14:12.310
remember being so thirsty that I got out

00:14:12.320 --> 00:14:13.829
of the car.

00:14:13.839 --> 00:14:15.750
I said, 'Sister, let's go over

00:14:15.760 --> 00:14:18.310
there. Let's see if we

00:14:18.320 --> 00:14:19.750
can find a quarter on the ground and

00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:21.590
maybe we can get a soda out of

00:14:21.590 --> 00:14:21.600
there.'So,

00:14:21.600 --> 00:14:23.750
we got out of the car and

00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:26.629
walked right up to that machine. And I

00:14:26.639 --> 00:14:29.189
remember there were no quarters, but I

00:14:29.199 --> 00:14:31.350
pushed a button and a soda came out of

00:14:31.360 --> 00:14:34.550
it. And my sister and I got so excited.

00:14:34.560 --> 00:14:36.550
It's imprinted in my brain forever.

00:14:36.560 --> 00:14:39.110
We rejoiced about that. She pushed a

00:14:39.120 --> 00:14:40.790
button and another one came out. Then I

00:14:40.800 --> 00:14:42.150
pushed another one and another one came

00:14:42.160 --> 00:14:45.269
out, and we loaded our arms full of sodas

00:14:45.279 --> 00:14:48.310
and they were cold. It was the best

00:14:48.320 --> 00:14:49.910
thing ever. So see, God

00:14:49.920 --> 00:14:52.230
knows the desires of your heart and

00:14:52.240 --> 00:14:56.310
your needs. It felt

00:14:56.320 --> 00:14:58.550
like a very spiritual day that

00:14:58.560 --> 00:15:01.590
day. We were so appreciative and

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:03.750
thankful and we just rejoiced as little

00:15:03.760 --> 00:15:05.269
kids. We were out there rejoicing, and

00:15:05.279 --> 00:15:08.230
we got enough for several

00:15:08.240 --> 00:15:10.389
Cokes for each of us. Then we

00:15:10.399 --> 00:15:11.750
stopped and were like, 'Hey,

00:15:11.760 --> 00:15:13.910
let's just go back to the car and

00:15:13.920 --> 00:15:16.310
drink them.'And it was the best day. It

00:15:16.320 --> 00:15:18.710
was the most refreshing soda I've ever

00:15:18.720 --> 00:15:22.629
had in my life. And it was one

00:15:22.629 --> 00:15:22.639
of

00:15:22.639 --> 00:15:24.870
those God moments and we just

00:15:24.880 --> 00:15:26.710
rejoiced at the little small

00:15:26.720 --> 00:15:30.069
things. When we didn't have enough

00:15:30.079 --> 00:15:31.990
money to pay our electric bills as

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:34.310
kids and they were turned off,

00:15:34.310 --> 00:15:34.320
and

00:15:34.320 --> 00:15:36.710
we didn't have food

00:15:36.720 --> 00:15:40.069
in our fridge, we would pray and we would have

00:15:41.920 --> 00:15:45.110
groceries show up on our doorstep.

00:15:45.120 --> 00:15:47.590
Countless times, I just

00:15:47.600 --> 00:15:49.829
remember so many small

00:15:49.839 --> 00:15:53.030
miracles and us

00:15:53.040 --> 00:15:56.230
being so excited about everything.

00:15:56.240 --> 00:15:59.030
It was just a lifestyle, you know? Even as

00:15:59.040 --> 00:16:01.590
a kid, we just got so excited about

00:16:01.600 --> 00:16:04.310
everything that the Lord did, big

00:16:04.320 --> 00:16:06.230
or small.

00:16:07.120 --> 00:16:09.670
Christmas presents one time...

00:16:09.680 --> 00:16:11.590
we had Christmas presents show up.

00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:13.350
Somebody came and just showed up in the

00:16:13.360 --> 00:16:14.629
middle of the night. We were

00:16:14.639 --> 00:16:16.710
sleeping on the floor

00:16:16.710 --> 00:16:16.720
somewhere—I

00:16:16.720 --> 00:16:18.389
vaguely remember it because I was

00:16:18.399 --> 00:16:21.030
so little—but I remember them showing up

00:16:21.040 --> 00:16:24.790
with Christmas presents,

00:16:24.800 --> 00:16:26.949
beautifully wrapped, just beautiful. And

00:16:26.959 --> 00:16:28.389
I remember one of the best

00:16:28.399 --> 00:16:30.470
Christmases I ever had. And it wasn't

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:32.150
even necessarily a whole lot of

00:16:32.160 --> 00:16:34.389
them. It was just that we didn't have

00:16:34.399 --> 00:16:36.710
anything. So we were

00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:39.430
just so thankful and appreciative.

00:16:39.440 --> 00:16:40.949
Countless little things like that that

00:16:40.959 --> 00:16:43.749
I can remember. And even

00:16:43.759 --> 00:16:47.189
going in the line, we

00:16:47.199 --> 00:16:50.629
would be sitting at a gas

00:16:50.639 --> 00:16:53.829
station and my dad would run out of

00:16:53.839 --> 00:16:55.749
gas all the time

00:16:55.759 --> 00:16:57.430
because we didn't have any money for

00:16:57.440 --> 00:17:00.310
anything. I remember us barely

00:17:00.320 --> 00:17:02.230
making it to a gas station one time and

00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:04.390
then someone just would pay for our gas

00:17:04.400 --> 00:17:05.829
and they would say, 'You know

00:17:05.829 --> 00:17:05.839
what...'I

00:17:05.839 --> 00:17:07.110
feel like I'm supposed to pay for your

00:17:07.120 --> 00:17:10.230
gas today. It was miracle after miracle. And

00:17:10.240 --> 00:17:12.309
you know, it doesn't have to be a big

00:17:12.319 --> 00:17:14.549
miracle to be a miracle. It's that God

00:17:14.559 --> 00:17:16.069
is in everything. He's in the small

00:17:16.079 --> 00:17:17.990
things. He's in the big things. And

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:19.829
we were just being thankful for

00:17:19.839 --> 00:17:21.829
everything.

00:17:21.839 --> 00:17:23.029
It's beautiful.

00:17:23.039 --> 00:17:25.429
I love it. There were so many times,

00:17:25.439 --> 00:17:27.429
even since we've been married,

00:17:27.439 --> 00:17:29.270
that we didn't have anything

00:17:29.270 --> 00:17:29.280
and

00:17:29.280 --> 00:17:31.590
we were trying to

00:17:31.600 --> 00:17:34.710
figure out how to pay our electric bill.

00:17:34.710 --> 00:17:34.720
I

00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:35.430
told

00:17:35.440 --> 00:17:38.230
Diana, "We

00:17:38.240 --> 00:17:39.909
don't have enough money this month to

00:17:39.919 --> 00:17:41.669
pay our electric bill because it was

00:17:41.679 --> 00:17:43.990
summer and our electric was

00:17:43.990 --> 00:17:44.000
higher."When

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:45.669
you're working for a church—we worked

00:17:45.669 --> 00:17:45.679
for a church—we

00:17:45.679 --> 00:17:48.789
made

00:17:48.799 --> 00:17:51.990
barely anything. It was

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:54.070
rough living on food stamps.

00:17:54.080 --> 00:17:56.230
I was a janitor there for a long time

00:17:56.240 --> 00:17:59.190
and we struggled. There

00:17:59.190 --> 00:17:59.200
were

00:17:59.200 --> 00:18:01.590
times whenever we got paid every

00:18:01.600 --> 00:18:03.909
two weeks and we would have it all spent

00:18:03.919 --> 00:18:07.430
before we got it by borrowing on a

00:18:07.440 --> 00:18:09.190
credit card or whatever we could do to

00:18:09.200 --> 00:18:09.990
just make it.

00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:12.150
Our bills took up our entire

00:18:12.160 --> 00:18:14.070
paycheck, so it would be already spent.

00:18:14.080 --> 00:18:15.510
We already knew what that went to:

00:18:15.520 --> 00:18:17.669
trying to get therapy for Megan,

00:18:17.679 --> 00:18:19.590
trying to get her speech or whatever.

00:18:19.600 --> 00:18:21.190
The government would only

00:18:21.200 --> 00:18:22.710
cover so much

00:18:22.710 --> 00:18:22.720
because

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:25.750
it was expensive. We

00:18:25.760 --> 00:18:27.990
thought, "Well, what are we going to

00:18:27.990 --> 00:18:28.000
do?"So

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:29.990
we were so desperate to try to

00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:33.270
help Megan at that time, just trying

00:18:33.280 --> 00:18:36.310
to find any kind of alternative

00:18:36.320 --> 00:18:39.669
to help her to function more

00:18:39.679 --> 00:18:41.510
because we wanted her to live

00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:45.990
a normal life. It was rough. We

00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:48.230
charged everything up. We were tens of

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:49.909
thousands of dollars in credit card

00:18:49.919 --> 00:18:51.350
debt. And back then, whenever you're

00:18:51.360 --> 00:18:53.669
making what we made, it looked like a

00:18:53.679 --> 00:18:55.029
mountain. So, you had to

00:18:55.039 --> 00:18:56.630
file bankruptcy. You do everything you

00:18:56.640 --> 00:18:58.789
can to just get through because we

00:18:58.799 --> 00:19:00.230
didn't have food.

00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:01.430
There would be times we'd be like, "Man,

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:02.710
what are we going to do?"And so there

00:19:02.710 --> 00:19:02.720
was

00:19:02.720 --> 00:19:04.150
always grandma; she'd make

00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:06.310
you a meal or buy you a pizza or

00:19:06.320 --> 00:19:08.950
surprise you. Things that God would put

00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:10.870
on her heart and she wouldn't even know.

00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:13.510
We've never been a

00:19:13.520 --> 00:19:17.990
people to give a "ministry of hints"or

00:19:17.990 --> 00:19:18.000
say,

00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:20.470
"Hey, we're having a hard

00:19:20.470 --> 00:19:20.480
time,"because

00:19:20.480 --> 00:19:23.430
we believe by faith.

00:19:23.440 --> 00:19:25.110
We're not going to go around talking

00:19:25.120 --> 00:19:27.350
about our problems to everybody and

00:19:27.360 --> 00:19:29.909
telling them how bad you've got it,

00:19:29.919 --> 00:19:31.590
because it's just like

00:19:31.600 --> 00:19:33.590
this: I try to tell y'all, pray in the

00:19:33.600 --> 00:19:35.909
spirit and don't let the devil see

00:19:35.919 --> 00:19:37.990
that he's made a move on you

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:40.230
that's working, that you feel like it's

00:19:40.240 --> 00:19:43.430
beating you down. Keep your head above water

00:19:43.430 --> 00:19:43.440
and give

00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:45.350
God praise for every little

00:19:45.360 --> 00:19:47.430
thing. So I'd just sit on the couch just

00:19:47.440 --> 00:19:49.350
like I'm doing right now—and my

00:19:49.360 --> 00:19:51.590
son can testify to this because he'd get

00:19:51.600 --> 00:19:55.430
in there with us and Diana—and say, "God, I

00:19:55.440 --> 00:19:57.029
just want to say thank you that our

00:19:57.039 --> 00:19:59.110
water bill's paid

00:19:59.110 --> 00:19:59.120
tonight,"and

00:19:59.120 --> 00:20:04.310
I would spend my whole

00:20:04.320 --> 00:20:07.430
night giving

00:20:07.440 --> 00:20:10.390
God praise for the water bill. "God, I

00:20:10.400 --> 00:20:11.990
thank you for the water bill."Anyway,

00:20:11.990 --> 00:20:12.000
it was

00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:14.630
only a $100 water bill or trash

00:20:14.630 --> 00:20:14.640
or

00:20:14.640 --> 00:20:16.549
whatever; it's not very much, but it was

00:20:16.559 --> 00:20:20.150
a lot to us. And we would take a seed

00:20:20.160 --> 00:20:22.870
and we would sow what we could. And we

00:20:22.880 --> 00:20:24.710
didn't have a seed because the Bible says,

00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:26.470
"Give and it shall be given unto you;

00:20:26.480 --> 00:20:27.990
good measure, pressed down, shaken

00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:29.270
together, and running over will it give

00:20:29.280 --> 00:20:31.270
unto your bosom."And it was required

00:20:31.280 --> 00:20:35.110
for us to tithe as staff. And

00:20:35.120 --> 00:20:36.630
after you tithed, we didn't want to

00:20:36.640 --> 00:20:37.909
tithe because we were like, "We don't

00:20:37.919 --> 00:20:39.750
have enough money to eat,

00:20:39.750 --> 00:20:39.760
really."But

00:20:39.760 --> 00:20:42.470
it was required to tithe. So we would

00:20:42.480 --> 00:20:46.549
believe by faith to get through

00:20:46.559 --> 00:20:48.230
to the next week after you tithed.

00:20:48.230 --> 00:20:48.240
You'd

00:20:48.240 --> 00:20:49.750
think, "Man, even if

00:20:49.760 --> 00:20:51.990
it was $200 for tithe because

00:20:52.000 --> 00:20:53.990
we didn't make much,"you're thinking this

00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:55.669
is a lot because it would have paid

00:20:55.669 --> 00:20:55.679
the

00:20:55.679 --> 00:20:57.350
electric or maybe something.

00:20:57.360 --> 00:20:59.909
But I trusted God and I would

00:20:59.919 --> 00:21:02.310
ask the Lord, "God, show me and give me a

00:21:02.320 --> 00:21:04.950
creative idea to get wealth."And that's

00:21:04.960 --> 00:21:06.230
where I always asked Him, "Father, you're

00:21:06.240 --> 00:21:07.029
going to have to take

00:21:07.039 --> 00:21:10.950
care of us."And He would always provide.

00:21:10.960 --> 00:21:13.350
We always got through. I would sow a

00:21:13.360 --> 00:21:16.149
seed and I would use my

00:21:16.159 --> 00:21:17.909
faith. I would sow a seed and it would

00:21:17.919 --> 00:21:20.149
provide for that need. He always

00:21:20.149 --> 00:21:20.159
took

00:21:20.159 --> 00:21:22.070
care of us. And we got to the point where we

00:21:22.080 --> 00:21:23.990
started sowing a little bit more, a

00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:26.230
little bit more. And I

00:21:26.240 --> 00:21:29.029
realized that the Lord started teaching

00:21:29.039 --> 00:21:31.669
me about good ground,

00:21:31.679 --> 00:21:33.270
because not all ground's going to

00:21:33.280 --> 00:21:35.990
produce. Most people don't want to hear

00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:37.830
that. And a lot of people go, "Well,

00:21:37.840 --> 00:21:40.149
that's not biblical."No, no, no, no. Some

00:21:40.149 --> 00:21:40.159
thirty,

00:21:40.159 --> 00:21:42.870
some sixty, and some hundredfold. And I'd

00:21:42.880 --> 00:21:44.630
always ask the Lord, "Show me where

00:21:44.640 --> 00:21:48.950
miracle good soil ground is. Show Diana

00:21:48.960 --> 00:21:52.710
and I where amazing ground is, because

00:21:52.720 --> 00:21:55.190
God, I need a quick harvest like

00:21:55.190 --> 00:21:55.200
Miracle-Gro.

00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:57.669
I need this seed to produce fast.

00:21:57.679 --> 00:21:59.270
I don't need it to be in the ground for

00:21:59.280 --> 00:22:01.669
weeks at a time and us receive six

00:22:01.679 --> 00:22:03.430
months or a year from now. I need it

00:22:03.440 --> 00:22:06.470
tomorrow. I need a miracle

00:22:06.470 --> 00:22:06.480
tomorrow."And

00:22:06.480 --> 00:22:08.390
so I started just praying and asking

00:22:08.400 --> 00:22:10.390
Him, "Show me, Father,"and just praying in

00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:11.990
the spirit, "Show me, Father, I thank you,

00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:13.909
